<h4>5.3.4 galIdeas</h4>
<table>
<tr><th>Property</th><th>Value</th></tr>
<tr><td>Control Type</td><td>Gallery@2.15.0</td></tr>
<tr><td>Variant</td><td>BrowseLayout_Vertical_TwoTextOneImageVariant_ver5.0</td></tr>
<tr><td>Position</td><td>X: 537, Y: 162</td></tr>
<tr><td>Data Source</td><td>AI_Idea (Dataverse: <code>cr39e_aiidea</code>)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sort</td><td>CreatedAt descending (newest first)</td></tr>
</table>

<p><b>Gallery Items Formula:</b></p>
<div class="callout">
<code style="white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 9pt;">SortByColumns(
    Filter(
        AI_Idea,
        // Search filter
        Or(
            IsBlank(txtIdeasSearch.Text),
            txtIdeasSearch.Text = "",
            Title in txtIdeasSearch.Text,
            Text(AICapabilityArea) in txtIdeasSearch.Text,
            Text(BusinessFunction) in txtIdeasSearch.Text
        ),
        // Status filter
        Or(
            IsBlank(ddStatusFilter.Selected.Value),
            ddStatusFilter.Selected.Value = "All",
            Text(Status) = ddStatusFilter.Selected.Value
        ),
        // Business Function filter
        Or(
            IsBlank(ddFunctionFilter.Selected.Value),
            ddFunctionFilter.Selected.Value = "All",
            Text(BusinessFunction) = ddFunctionFilter.Selected.Value
        )
    ),
    "CreatedAt",
    SortOrder.Descending
)</code>
</div>

<p><b>Gallery Template Controls:</b></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Control Name</th><th>Type</th><th>Bound To</th><th>Details</th></tr>
<tr><td>Image1</td><td>Image@2.2.3</td><td>(no image set)</td><td>72 &times; 72 px, border-radius: 8px, vertically centred</td></tr>
<tr><td>Title1</td><td>Label@2.5.1</td><td><code>ThisItem.SampleHeading</code></td><td>Size 14, Segoe UI, semibold when selected. <b>Note:</b> Still bound to gallery sample data, not <code>ThisItem.Title</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Subtitle1</td><td>Label@2.5.1</td><td><code>ThisItem.SampleText</code></td><td>Size 12, grey text. <b>Note:</b> Still bound to gallery sample data</td></tr>
<tr><td>Title</td><td>Label@2.5.1</td><td><code>ThisItem.Title</code></td><td>Custom label bound to actual idea Title</td></tr>
<tr><td>CapabilityArea</td><td>Label@2.5.1</td><td><code>Text(ThisItem.AICapabilityArea)</code></td><td>Displays the AI Capability Area choice value as text</td></tr>
<tr><td>Label3</td><td>Label@2.5.1</td><td>(no text set)</td><td>Empty label at position (40, 40)</td></tr>
<tr><td>StatusBadge</td><td>Classic/Button@2.2.0</td><td><code>Text(ThisItem.Status)</code></td><td>Colour-coded via Switch formula (see Section 6.2)</td></tr>
<tr><td>NextArrow1</td><td>Classic/Icon@2.5.0</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>ChevronRight icon, 50 &times; 50 px, tooltip: "View item details"</td></tr>
<tr><td>Separator1</td><td>Rectangle@2.3.0</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>White bar (8px height) between gallery items</td></tr>
<tr><td>Rectangle1</td><td>Rectangle@2.3.0</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Blue selection indicator (4px wide), visible only when <code>ThisItem.IsSelected</code></td></tr>
</table>

<div class="callout-yellow">
<b>Observation:</b> The gallery template's <code>Title1</code> and <code>Subtitle1</code> labels are still bound to the default sample data properties (<code>ThisItem.SampleHeading</code>, <code>ThisItem.SampleText</code>) rather than to actual Dataverse columns. The custom <code>Title</code> and <code>CapabilityArea</code> labels were added separately and are correctly bound to real data.
</div>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 6. BUSINESS LOGIC & FORMULAS -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>6. Business Logic &amp; Formulas</h2>

<h3>6.1 App OnStart (App.StartScreen)</h3>
<p>The following initialisation logic runs when the app starts:</p>
<div class="callout">
<code style="white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 9.5pt;">// Initialize app-level variables
Set(currentUser, User());
Set(scoreThreshold, 2);

// Score mapping table (used in assessment calculations)
ClearCollect(
    colScoreMap,
    {Level: "low", Value: 1},
    {Level: "medium", Value: 2},
    {Level: "high", Value: 3}
);</code>
</div>

<table>
<tr><th>Variable / Collection</th><th>Type</th><th>Value</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>currentUser</code></td><td>Variable (Record)</td><td><code>User()</code></td><td>Stores the current logged-in user&rsquo;s profile (display name, email, image)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>scoreThreshold</code></td><td>Variable (Number)</td><td><code>2</code></td><td>The threshold value used for quadrant determination (&ge; 2 = High)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>colScoreMap</code></td><td>Collection (Table)</td><td>3 rows: low=1, medium=2, high=3</td><td>Lookup table mapping score level text to numeric values for assessment calculations</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="callout-yellow">
<b>Observation:</b> The <code>colScoreMap</code> collection uses <b>lowercase</b> level names ("low", "medium", "high"), but the Dataverse Choice values for the assessment dimensions store <b>capitalised</b> labels ("Low", "Medium", "High"). Any formula using <code>colScoreMap</code> for lookups will need to account for this case mismatch (e.g., use <code>Lower()</code> or update the collection to use capitalised values).
</div>

<h3>6.2 Status Badge Colour Logic</h3>
<p>The <code>StatusBadge</code> button in the gallery uses a Switch formula to apply a unique colour to each of the 11 idea lifecycle statuses:</p>
<div class="callout">
<code style="white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 9.5pt;">Switch(
    Text(ThisItem.Status),
    "Submitted",    ColorValue("#6C757D"),
    "Screening",    ColorValue("#17A2B8"),
    "Assessment",   ColorValue("#483698"),
    "Prioritized",  ColorValue("#00A3A1"),
    "Development",  ColorValue("#FFC107"),
    "Pilot",        ColorValue("#FF6B35"),
    "Deployed",     ColorValue("#28A745"),
    "Scaling",      ColorValue("#00338D"),
    "On Hold",      ColorValue("#ADB5BD"),
    "Rejected",     ColorValue("#DC3545"),
    "Archived",     ColorValue("#343A40"),
    ColorValue("#6C757D")  // fallback
)</code>
</div>

<table>
<tr><th>Status</th><th>Colour</th><th>Swatch</th></tr>
<tr><td>Submitted</td><td>#6C757D</td><td style="background-color:#6C757D; color:white; text-align:center;">Grey</td></tr>
<tr><td>Screening</td><td>#17A2B8</td><td style="background-color:#17A2B8; color:white; text-align:center;">Teal</td></tr>
<tr><td>Assessment</td><td>#483698</td><td style="background-color:#483698; color:white; text-align:center;">Purple</td></tr>
<tr><td>Prioritized</td><td>#00A3A1</td><td style="background-color:#00A3A1; color:white; text-align:center;">KPMG Teal</td></tr>
<tr><td>Development</td><td>#FFC107</td><td style="background-color:#FFC107; color:black; text-align:center;">Amber</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pilot</td><td>#FF6B35</td><td style="background-color:#FF6B35; color:white; text-align:center;">Orange</td></tr>
<tr><td>Deployed</td><td>#28A745</td><td style="background-color:#28A745; color:white; text-align:center;">Green</td></tr>
<tr><td>Scaling</td><td>#00338D</td><td style="background-color:#00338D; color:white; text-align:center;">KPMG Blue</td></tr>
<tr><td>On Hold</td><td>#ADB5BD</td><td style="background-color:#ADB5BD; color:black; text-align:center;">Light Grey</td></tr>
<tr><td>Rejected</td><td>#DC3545</td><td style="background-color:#DC3545; color:white; text-align:center;">Red</td></tr>
<tr><td>Archived</td><td>#343A40</td><td style="background-color:#343A40; color:white; text-align:center;">Dark Grey</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>6.3 Gallery Filtering Logic</h3>
<p>The <code>galIdeas.Items</code> formula applies three filters in combination (AND logic):</p>
<ol>
    <li><b>Search filter</b>: If <code>txtIdeasSearch</code> has text, matches against Title, AI Capability Area, or Business Function using the <code>in</code> operator</li>
    <li><b>Status filter</b>: If <code>ddStatusFilter</code> is not "All", matches the idea&rsquo;s Status text exactly</li>
    <li><b>Function filter</b>: If <code>ddFunctionFilter</code> is not "All", matches the idea&rsquo;s Business Function text exactly</li>
</ol>
<p>Results are sorted by <code>CreatedAt</code> descending (newest ideas first).</p>

<div class="callout-yellow">
<b>Delegation Note:</b> The <code>in</code> operator used for search is <b>non-delegable</b> in Dataverse. This means the search filter will only operate on the first 2,000 records (or the configured delegation limit). If the AI Ideas table grows beyond this limit, a delegable alternative (e.g., <code>StartsWith</code> or Dataverse views) should be considered.
</div>

