<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 9. ASSUMPTIONS & CONSTRAINTS -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>9. Assumptions &amp; Constraints</h2>

<h3>9.1 Assumptions</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Users have Microsoft 365 licences with Power Apps access and connectivity to the Dataverse environment at <code>org49a69cf1.crm15.dynamics.com</code>.</li>
    <li>The Dataverse tables and their columns/choice-sets are considered stable and will not change structurally during the remaining build phase.</li>
    <li>The application will remain a Canvas App (not converted to a Model-driven app).</li>
</ol>

<h3>9.2 Constraints</h3>
<ol>
    <li><b>Non-delegable search:</b> The <code>in</code> operator in the gallery Items formula is not delegable to Dataverse, limiting search to the first 2,000 records.</li>
    <li><b>Case mismatch:</b> The <code>colScoreMap</code> collection uses lowercase level names ("low") while Dataverse stores capitalised labels ("Low"). This must be resolved before the assessment screen is built.</li>
    <li><b>Gallery template bindings:</b> Two labels (<code>Title1</code>, <code>Subtitle1</code>) still reference gallery sample data (<code>SampleHeading</code>, <code>SampleText</code>) and need to be rebound to actual Dataverse columns.</li>
    <li><b>Fixed layout:</b> The app is designed for 1366 &times; 768 tablet form factor. No responsive behaviour is configured.</li>
</ol>

<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- 10. GLOSSARY -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->

<h2>10. Glossary</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Term</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>BRD</b></td><td>Business Requirements Document &mdash; describes the business needs and current state of a system.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Canvas App</b></td><td>A Power Apps application type where the maker controls every pixel of the layout and formula logic.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Dataverse</b></td><td>Microsoft&rsquo;s cloud data platform providing structured storage, role-based security, and business logic for Power Platform apps.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Delegation</b></td><td>The mechanism by which Power Apps offloads filter/sort operations to Dataverse server-side. Non-delegable operations process only the first N rows locally.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Power Fx</b></td><td>The low-code formula language used in Power Apps, inspired by Excel formulas.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Option Set</b></td><td>A Dataverse column type that presents a fixed list of choices (also called Choice/Choices).</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Publisher Prefix</b></td><td>A short string (e.g., <code>cr39e_</code>) prepended to all custom table and column logical names, identifying the solution publisher.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Quadrant</b></td><td>One of four strategic classifications (Likely Wins, Calculated Risks, Marginal Gains, Avoid) based on Value and Feasibility score thresholds.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>colScoreMap</b></td><td>An in-memory Power Fx collection mapping score level labels (low/medium/high) to numeric values (1/2/3) for assessment calculations.</td></tr>
</table>

